  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency relief to drought affected communities in Zimbabwe - MEDRA</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Feeding into the ACT Alliance Appeal ZIM201 &quot;Emergency response to the drought in Zimbabwe&quot;, this project will focus on the WASH, climate smart agriculture, and psychosocial support components of the appeal. The project will target 17,000 direct beneficiaries affected by the humanitarian crisis in Zimbabwe, to meet their immediate emergency needs as well as enable them to be better prepared for future crises. This will be done through provision of emergency WASH support, as well as trainings in
climate smart agriculture to enable targeted households to better cope with the current as well as future droughts. Furthermore, the project will provide community members, faith leaders, and implementing partner staff with skills in community based psychosocial support in order to enhance the psychosocial wellbeing of affected communities.</narrative>
  </description>
